      "Appearance: Besalisks are stocky, bulky humanoids who evolved from large flightless avians, though they are often mistaken for reptilians due to their scales, sharp teeth, and long claws. Males sport prominent head crests and four arms; females can have up to eight. Sensory whiskers line their upper lip above a robust wattle. They sweat profusely in warm climates, being adapted to the frigid ocean world of Ojom.\nSociable Wanderers: Besalisks are chatty, fearless, and quick to form lasting friendships. They love adventure and thrill-seeking, but are notoriously unreliable \u2014 prone to walking off a job when bored and never coming back. Their loose lips and gossipy nature make them one of the galaxy's most frequently bounty-hunted species.\nUnderworld Connections: Though they avoid confrontation themselves, Besalisks have deep ties to the galactic underworld. Ojom escaped Imperial occupation by calling in favors with influential criminal contacts \u2014 debts many Besalisks spent years working off, especially those foolish enough to deal with the Hutts."
