      "Appearance: Chiss are near-Human in physiology, distinguished by blue skin, midnight-black hair, and glowing red eyes. Their coloration is believed to be caused by atmospheric minerals on their ice-locked homeworld Csilla, and their eyes glow more brightly in oxygen-rich atmospheres. They tend toward lean physiques due to a faster-than-average metabolism, reaching maturity around age ten or twelve.*\n\n*Strategic Minds: Chiss are proud and highly intelligent, valuing strategy and subterfuge over brute force. They are natural tacticians and pragmatists, qualities that led the Empire to single them out as potential allies despite its usual speciesism. A rare few have even achieved official rank in the Imperial military and Intelligence.*\n\n*Ascendancy: The Chiss govern themselves through the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions, maintaining isolation from the wider galaxy. While they cooperate with the Empire out of pragmatic recognition of shared values, they are not subservient \u2014 the Ascendancy retains self-governance and Chiss loyalty runs first to their own people.*"
