      "Appearance: Neimoidians resemble their Duros genetic cousins but tend toward grayer green-blue skin, with small forehead lumps, horizontally-split pupils, noseless faces, and down-turned mouths. Their skin becomes mottled under stress or self-indulgence, and their lung pods visibly expand and contract when anxious \u2014 leading to the saying they're the only species with an organ devoted to worrying. Elaborate hats, cloaks, and drapes signal rank and wealth; a Neimoidian is never seen hatless unless dead.\nGreed and Cowardice: Neimoidians are stereotyped across the galaxy as greedy, conniving, and fearful of death \u2014 a reputation largely earned through the Trade Federation's invasion of Naboo and alliance with the Separatists. They place tremendous value on wealth and material possessions, and will go to extraordinary lengths for profit while avoiding personal danger at all costs.\nSurvival of the Ruthless: Neimoidian grubs are raised in communal hives and deliberately given limited food, weeding out the weak. This brutal upbringing produces cunning survivors but also deeply insecure adults. Loyalty is considered one of the most difficult concepts for a Neimoidian to grasp, and they rely on droids for nearly everything to avoid personal risk."
